Adopted daughters
The names of the emperor's adoptive daughters, who were all second daughters of members of the Qing imperial clan, were titles, not personal names.267

Second-rank princess with no known title (1648&lt;U+2013&gt;1691/92), second daughter of Shunzhi's half-brother, Hong Taiji's fifth son &lt;U+0160&gt;ose (&lt;U+7855&gt;&lt;U+585E&gt;; 1629&lt;U+2013&gt;1655).268 Married in 1660 to Shang Kexi's son Shang Zhilong (&lt;U+5C1A&gt;&lt;U+4E4B&gt;&lt;U+9686&gt;).269
Second-rank princess Roujia &lt;U+67D4&gt;&lt;U+5609&gt; (1652&lt;U+2013&gt;1673), second daughter of Jirgalang's second son Jidu (&lt;U+6FDF&gt;&lt;U+5EA6&gt;; 1633&lt;U+2013&gt;1660). Married in 1663 to Geng Zhongming's (&lt;U+803F&gt;&lt;U+4EF2&gt;&lt;U+660E&gt;; 1604&lt;U+2013&gt;1649) grand-son Geng Juzhong (&lt;U+803F&gt;&lt;U+805A&gt;&lt;U+5FE0&gt;; 1650&lt;U+2013&gt;1687).270
Second-rank princess Duanmin &lt;U+7AEF&gt;&lt;U+654F&gt; (1653&lt;U+2013&gt;1729), second daughter of Yolo (&lt;U+5CB3&gt;&lt;U+6A02&gt;; 1625&lt;U+2013&gt;1689), fourth son of Qing founder Nurhaci's seventh son Abatai. Married in 1670 to Bandi (&lt;U+73ED&gt;&lt;U+7B2C&gt;; d. 1710), a Mongol of the Borjigit clan.271

